dt-option.default:
        The default value for the `-init searchPanes.viewTotal` paramater is `false`. 


        By setting the `-init searchPanes.viewTotal` parameter to true, the message displayed in the count column will change when a search is applied to the DataTable.

        As standard, SearchPanes will set the count column to display the total number of different values visible in the column when no filtering is taking place. When filtering is taking place the count column will display the number of entries that satisfy this condition currently on display followed by the total in the table which satisfy the condition in brackets.

        This is useful for keeping track of which options actually have entries present in the table when it has been searched upon.

        It is possible to adjust the messages shown both when searching is taking place and when it isn't, by using the `-init language.seearchPanes.count` and `-init language.searchPanes.countFiltered` options.






$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes:{
            viewTotal: true ,
        }
    });
});



-init language.searchPanes.count
-init language.searchPanes.countFiltered
